{% extends "_layouts/base" %}
{% import '_macros/global' as global %}

{% block content %}

    {# TEMP: Grab some random example content #}
    {% set entry = craft.entries.section('articles')[0] %}
    {% set placeholderImage = entry.articleHeroContent.one().image.one() %}
    {% set placeholderShortCopy = "Optional short support copy" %}

    {# Layout #}
    <section
        class="product-detail-layout | space-menu | flex-grid">

        {# Main #}
        <article class="entry-main">

            {# Nav #}
            {# Notes: This just links back out to all products of this type. Shouldn't be more than 1 link, but the markup is structured to accomodate future scaling. #}
                <nav aria-label="Browse all products in this section" class="breadcrumbs"> <ul class="list-reset">
                    <li>
                        <a class="link -underline -sm " href="#">
                            Shop / Books
                        </a>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </nav>

            {# Header #}
            <header class="entry__header" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Product">
                <h1 class="title | header-md | font-serif | mt-8" itemprop="name">The Christian Life: Cross or Glory</h1>
                <div class="detail | text-slate-light text-lg | mt-6" itemprop="description">
                    Steven D. Paulson & Scott L. Keith
                </div>
                <div class="price | text-slate-light text-lg | mt-2" itemprop="offers" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Offer">
                    <meta content="USD" itemprop="priceCurrency"/>
                    $<span class="amount" itemprop="price">4.99</span>
                </div>

                {# Purchase Form #}
                <form action="" class="form-base -purchase | mt-6">
                    <div class="form-group -start">
                        <div class="field-group">
                            <select_box :opt="{ name: 'format', variant: '-md' }">
                                <option selected value="All Formats">All Formats</option>
                                <option value="ebook">ebook</option>
                                <option value="Another">Another</option>
                            </select_box>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-group -start">
                        <div class="field-group">
                            <input min="1" type="number" value="1">
                        </div>
                        <div class="field-group">
                            <button class="btn -red -md">Add to Cart</button>
                        </div>
                    </div>


                </form>
            </header>

            {# Content Blocks #}
            <div class="entry__blocks">
                <div class="paragraphs -md -loose | article-content">
                    <p>This book offers a radically different perspective from that of many best-selling authors concerning how the Christian should measure and evaluate travel along Godâ€™s path of righteousness. It will endeavor to persuade the reader that by feeding regularly on the Gospel in the Preached Word and The Supper, God promises to have His way with the Christian and He alone will accomplish all that is needed for life in Him to be complete. He is not waiting or requiring you to do anything first (during or after) to provide you with every blessing of the Gospel.</p>
                    <p>The audio book version of this title is available through these retailers:</p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>Amazon</li>
                        <li>Audible</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>

        {# Aside #}
        <div
            class="entry-aside">

            {# TEMP: Use `page-hero--media` partial #}
            {{ global.image( placeholderImage, '-fit-cover' )}}

        </div>

    </section>

{% endblock %}
